Prefer match clauses over if statements.
Use modern idiomatic ocaml syntax 'let*' when working with monads
Use the command 'make build' to test is the code compiles, and parse the output to find errors. This is the same as running 'dune build'
When adding signatures to functions, prefer the more generic style 'let fun x: 'a -> 'b = fun ...'
Keep comments short, and don't document obvious arguments or return values
Perfer using already enabled ppx'es
Dont use for loops. Find a way to convert results into list and iterate / fold over the list
Avoid use of reference cells
